    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The present work concerns the COVID-19\u2019s spread over The United States, Brazil and Colombia. Although countries show differences in economic development, but similarities such as continental dimension or social interaction, the spread of COVID-19 in them has some similarities. At the moment, the countries are living the disease with temporal delay. Thus, we used a database on WHO Coronavirus, Mathematical Modeling and Numerical Simulations to describe the most recent COVID-19 development patterns in these countries, which we saw.</jats:p>",
